Topics:
    -Basics for making a script
        -Pick a shell interpreter
        -Declare it
        -Make the file executable
            -Alternative ways of running the script
        -What happens now?  A subshell is launched, and your commands run sequentially within that subshell
    -Special characters
        -I will use many of these, but I won't cover them explicitly, please read up on them independantly and reach out with questions
        -http://www.tldp.org/LDP/abs/html/special-chars.html
    -Basic Shell variables
        -$1 $2 etc
        -!$ $* $@ (More on arrays later)
        -Intro to quoting (by example)
    -Using a command within a script
        -Why you use full path
    -Capture a command output in a variable (exit code for success, or value for later use)
    -Control Structure Basics
        -Test (if/else)
        -Loop basics (for loops)




References:
    BASH Scripting: http://www.tldp.org/LDP/abs/html/index.html (Old version:http://tldp.org/HOWTO/Bash-Prog-Intro-HOWTO.html)
    Internal Shell Variables: http://www.tldp.org/LDP/abs/html/internalvariables.html








